<task id="WKSP-004" project="spaarke-workspace-user-configuration-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Define sprk_workspacelayout Dataverse entity schema</title>
    <phase>1</phase>
    <tags>dataverse, schema</tags>
    <estimated-effort>1h</estimated-effort>
    <rigor-level>MINIMAL</rigor-level>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>serial</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    <role>Senior TypeScript/C# developer implementing workspace personalization</role>
    <goal>Define the sprk_workspacelayout Dataverse entity schema documentation and deployment reference for the workspace layout persistence entity.</goal>
    <context>
      User workspace layouts are persisted in Dataverse as sprk_workspacelayout records. Each record stores
      the layout template ID, the sections JSON (array of section placements with slot indices), a display
      name, whether it's the user's default layout, and a sort order for the workspace switcher.

      The entity uses Owner security model so each user owns their own layout records. The BFF API reads
      and writes these records via Dataverse Web API. The sections JSON is a multiline text column storing
      a JSON array of {sectionId, slotIndex} objects — no serialized JSX or component references.

      This task creates the entity definition documentation and any solution XML or metadata files needed
      for entity deployment to the Dataverse dev environment.
    </context>
    <constraints>
      - Entity logical name MUST be sprk_workspacelayout with publisher prefix "sprk"
      - Primary key: sprk_workspacelayoutid (GUID, auto-generated)
      - MUST use Owner security model (sprk_ownerid via standard ownership)
      - sprk_sectionsjson MUST be Multiline Text with max length (1048576) to accommodate large section arrays
      - sprk_name MUST be String with max length 100
      - sprk_layouttemplateid MUST be String with max length 50
      - sprk_isdefault MUST be Boolean (default: false)
      - sprk_sortorder MUST be Integer (default: 0)
      - MUST document the JSON schema for sprk_sectionsjson content
      - Entity MUST be included in the Spaarke unmanaged solution for deployment
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/constraints/data.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <relevant-files>
    <file>projects/spaarke-workspace-user-configuration-r1/</file>
  </relevant-files>
  <steps>
    <step id="1">Create entity schema definition file at projects/spaarke-workspace-user-configuration-r1/notes/entity-schema-sprk_workspacelayout.md documenting all columns, types, constraints, and the JSON schema for sprk_sectionsjson.</step>
    <step id="2">Document the column definitions: sprk_workspacelayoutid (Uniqueidentifier PK), sprk_name (String 100, required, display name), sprk_layouttemplateid (String 50, required), sprk_sectionsjson (Multiline 1048576, required), sprk_isdefault (Boolean, default false), sprk_sortorder (WholeNumber, default 0).</step>
    <step id="3">Document the sprk_sectionsjson JSON schema: array of objects with "sectionId" (string, matches SectionRegistration.id) and "slotIndex" (integer, 0-based position in template slots).</step>
    <step id="4">Document the security model: Owner-based access, users can only CRUD their own layouts. System workspaces are defined in code, not stored in this entity.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Entity schema document exists with all 6 custom columns fully specified (name, type, constraints, defaults)</criterion>
    <criterion>JSON schema for sprk_sectionsjson is documented with example payload</criterion>
    <criterion>Security model (Owner) is documented with access control expectations</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
